properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 21 at 11:21PM CST until January 22 at 9:00AM CST by NWS Twin Cities/Chanhassen MN
properties.description:
...MIXED WINTRY PRECIPITATION EXPECTED OVERNIGHT THROUGH THE
WEDNESDAY MORNING COMMUTE...

.A mixture of light snow and freezing rain, possibly also mixed
with sleet, will spread northward over southern Minnesota then
eastward into west central Wisconsin. Areas impacted in Minnesota
will be those along and south of a line from Sleepy Eye to
Winthrop to Belle Plaine to Cottage Grove. This includes the
Interstate 90 corridor and the Interstate 35 corridor south of
the Twin Cities. Areas impacted in Wisconsin will be those along
and south of a line from New Richmond to Cornell. This includes
the Interstate 94 corridor. A Winter Weather Advisory is in
effect overnight through late Wednesday morning.

Snow accumulations of less than an inch combined with a few
hundredths of an inch of ice accumulation will result in slippery
travel conditions, especially during the overnight hours when icy
patches will be difficult to see. The Wednesday morning commute
will also be impacted. Motorists are urged to allow extra time to
reach destinations, use extra caution and reduce speed due to
expected slippery road conditions.

* WHAT...Mixed precipitation expected. Total snow accumulations of
up to 1 inch and ice accumulations of a few hundredths to a
tenth of an inch.

* WHERE...Portions of central, east central, south central and
southeast Minnesota.

* WHEN...Until 9 AM CST Wednesday.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. The hazardous
conditions could impact the Wednesday morning commute.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 9 AM CST WEDNESDAY
